    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-16T05:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-16T05:16:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.7131/83: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-16T12:00:00+01:44"
                            >January 16, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Department’s telegram No. 19, Dec. 11, 6 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d737fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1929v03#pg_755">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 755</ref>.</note> Note from Foreign
                    Office states that, owing to numerous commercial treaties under negotiation,
                    Rumanian Government will only in February be able to begin negotiations with
                    United States. Department’s draft treaty still being studied but Legation will
                    be furnished next week with draft of treaty proposed by Rumania. Note adds
                    Rumanian Government desires to conclude consular convention at same time as
                    commercial.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
